# Cursor IDE Rules for AUTOWAIS Project

## Project Context
This is a Next.js 15 website for AUTOWAIS, a professional web solutions company.

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Follow React functional components with hooks
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Prefer const over let/var
- Use arrow functions for components

## File Structure
- Components in `/src/components/`
- Pages in `/src/app/`
- Data in `/src/data/`
- Images in `/public/images/`
- Types in `/src/types/`

## Key Technologies
- Next.js 15 (App Router)
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- React 18
- Framer Motion (for animations)

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `BlogCard.tsx`)
- Files: kebab-case (e.g., `blog-posts.ts`)
- CSS classes: Tailwind utility classes

## Development Guidelines
- Always include proper TypeScript types
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Ensure accessibility (alt tags, ARIA labels)
- Optimize images and assets
- Follow responsive design principles

## Common Patterns
- Use `'use client'` for client-side components
- Export components as default
- Import types with `import type`
- Use proper error boundaries 